Dr '''Kieron O'Hara''' is a [[philosopher]], [[computer scientist]] and political writer. He is currently a senior research fellow within the department of Electronics and Computer Science at the [[University of Southampton]] where he specialises in the politics, philosophy and [[epistemology]] of technology<ref>http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/about/kieron_o_hara.php</ref><ref>http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/people/kmo</ref>. 

Other projects have included co-authoring the script of ''[[Tomb Raider 4]]''<ref>http://eprints.ecs.soton.ac.uk/12489/</ref> and an article in the ''[[Journal of Popular Culture]]'' on the film ''[[Carry On Cabby]]''<ref>http://eprints.ecs.soton.ac.uk/4146/</ref>


==Selected Bibliography==

*''Plato and the Internet'' (2002) ISBN 1-84046-346-5
*''Trust: From Socrates to Spin'' (2004) ISBN 1-84046-531-X
*''After Blair: Conservatism Beyond Thatcher'' (2005) ISBN 1-84046-594-8 
*''The Referendum Roundabout'' (2006) ISBN 1-84540-040-2 
*''inequality.com: Power, Poverty and the Digital Divide'' (2006, with David Stevens) ISBN 1-85168-450-6 
*''After Blair: David Cameron and the Conservative Tradition'' (2007) ISBN 1-84046-795-9

